# SyncBeat

Real-time synchronized music listening app. Two friends call each other, one picks a song, and both hear it in perfect sync.

## Stack

**Server** (`/server`): Node.js + TypeScript, Express 5, Socket.io 4, PostgreSQL (Drizzle/Neon), Upstash Redis (`rediss://`, ioredis), Cloudflare R2, JWT + bcrypt, Resend, Expo Push, yt-dlp.

**Client** (`/client`): Expo SDK 55 + React Native 0.83, expo-router, expo-av, expo-secure-store, socket.io-client, axios, local useState (zustand installed but unused).

## Database Tables

| Table | Key columns |
|---|---|
| `users` | id, name, username, email, passwordHash, pushToken, isOnline, lastSeenAt |
| `friendships` | senderId, receiverId, status (pending/accepted/declined/blocked) |
| `tracks` | uploaderId, title, artist, duration, fileUrl, mimeType, isPublic, externalId, externalSource, previewUrl |
| `liked_tracks` | userId, trackId |
| `call_sessions` | callerId, receiverId, status (ringing/active/ended/missed/declined) |
| `sync_sessions` | callSessionId, trackId, hostId, isPlaying, positionSecs, scheduledAt |
| `listen_history` | userId, trackId, listenedWithId, callSessionId, durationSecs |
| `otp_codes` | email, code, used, expiresAt |
